title: Bad if your language puts accented letters at the end of the dictionary
comment: This app's word search feature does not make the difference between accented and non-accented versions of letters. This doesn't matter in a language like French, where accents don't change the alphabetical order (école and eau are both in the E-section). But it does matter in a language like Norwegian, in which the letters å, æ, and ø are placed at the end of the dictionary. This makes it impossible to find any word with an å, æ, or ø with the search feature, since it'll send you to a, ae, and o respectively.
